documentation.text:
Mints stable coin to the vault contract.
 @param amountToMint The amount of stable coin to mint.

@notice Allows a user to deposit cUSD collateral in exchange for some amount of zUSD.
@param amountToDeposit  The amount of cUSD the user sent in the transaction

params.amountToDeposit: The amount of cUSD the user sent in the transaction

params.amountToMint: The amount of stable coin to mint.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

deposit(uint256).notice: Allows a user to deposit cUSD collateral in exchange for some amount of zUSD.

mint(uint256).notice: Mints stable coin to the vault contract.
